eu.linksmart.caf.cm.rules
Class DeclaredType

java.lang.Object
  eu.linksmart.caf.cm.rules.DeclaredType
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class DeclaredType
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Defines a type declared inline in the ContextRuleSet, that can then be used.

Variable members of the type are defined with Attributes (id = name, value = type).

MetaAttributes of the declared type can also be provided (See DROOLS Documentatin).

The factRole of the type declares how it should be handled - as a 'fact', or as an 'event'.

Author:
Michael Crouch
